name: Hammered Bronze Band
description:
▴ The band was hand sculpted from bronze metal and fired in the the kiln. Rugged, rustic and organic. Hammered and slightly aged with a teal patina. The little imperfections are what give this band uniqueness and character. 

▴ The piece is coated in a wax finish but will slightly patina and darken over time. Approximately 10mm in width. (If you'd like it wider or more narrow let us know in the 'notes' section of checkout) 

▴ Our rings come with a break line on the inside of the band. A break line is is soft groove that doesn't necessarily undermine the strength of the band, it simply creates a 'soft' spot. All of our bronze bands come this way, in case the band was to get stuck on an engine, while rock climbing, lifting guitar gear, etc. The point of a break line is that the ring will break so your finger doesn't. Perfect for you gnarly, rugged, manly-men. We can make another ring, we'd like you to keep all your fingers!

▴ Please read our shop policies before purchasing. Let us know if you have any questions!

© 2012 Christina Nicole

name: Herb Bundles
description:
Organic rosemary and sage grown in our garden. Hand harvested and dried in the studio. Wrapped in charming twines and yarns. 

Absolutely the best seasoning I've ever used. Throw out every other bit of rosemary you have, these bundles are SO rich and flavorful.

I hang mine in the kitchen. When it comes time for seasoning, holding both ends, I gently twist it over a sauté pan with a little salt and oil. Perfection with organic chicken, potatoes from the garden and some cabernet. 

You'll get 1 of these lovely large bundles.

name: Mens Bronze Band
description:
Travis's wedding band! He gets more compliments from women AND men on this ring.. men really love the rugged wilderness look to it. 

The band was hand sculpted from bronze metal and fired in the the kiln. The piece is rugged, rustic and organic. There are little imperfections in it which give it uniqueness and character. 

The band is about 9 mm wide but can be sculpted wider or shorter upon request, after purchase. The edges of the band are slightly rounded (called a 'comfort fit' ) to not catch on clothing or skin.. We're not fan's of the perfectly squared edge so we round the edge a bit. 

The piece is coated in a wax finish but will slightly patina and darken over time. Travis's has worn his for about a year and I shot the ring straight from his finger without cleaning, sanding or buffing. Your ring will be a little lighter in color, since it will be brand new and will gradually darken slightly.
